    <h1>Len&#xAD;ovo Smart Clock Es&#xAD;sen&#xAD;tial</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200909/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-09"><time>2020-09-09</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | TECH</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>$119, avail­able from Novem­ber</p>
    <p>The Google As­sis­tant-pow­ered smart clock is a mod­ern take on the tra­di­tional alarm clock.</p>
    <p>Be­sides the time, its old-school LED screen also shows the weather and tem­per­a­ture.</p>
    <p>Set your alarm us­ing the but­tons, or ask Google As­sis­tant to do it. Of course, Google As­sis­tant can also be used to con­trol other smart home de­vices or to play your favourite tunes through the clock’s 3W speaker.</p>
    <p>A nice touch – it has a USB port for charg­ing other de­vices.</p>

